# **Glitching**

## **Datamoshing**

One of the glitches I really want to recreate in VR is datamoshing. 

My HDCC106 seminar showed Takeshi Murata’s *Monster Movie* as an example of datamoshed glitch art.

[Takeshi Murata - Monster Movie](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=t1f3St51S9I)

In any medium that isn't digital video, you can’t really recreate datamoshing. Instead, you emulate the effect by making use of motion vectors.  
I’m still learning how exactly the process works, but I’m using the following as help for figuring out how to write the shaders.

[Creating Your Own Datamoshing Effect – ompuco](https://ompuco.wordpress.com/2018/03/29/creating-your-own-datamosh-effect/)   
[Datamoshing in URP : r/Unity3D](https://www.reddit.com/r/Unity3D/comments/160673g/datamoshing_in_urp/)   
[Datamoshing in VR](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=w_0pshfHgUk)

The last video was actually my inspiration for trying to do datamoshing in VR.

Something else I found out was that deleting I frames also messed with the audio. I’m not sure if I want to place a bigger focus on audio given my timeline, but it would be interesting to explore.

## **Image Corruption**

Another thing I did in my HDCC106 seminar was corrupt images by manipulating color data in the file. By deleting data, you can get some cool results:

I’m hoping the result will look nice.
